{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Wyoming", "text_new": "{{current event|date=March 2020}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Wyoming\n| width           = \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| map1            = \n| legend1         =\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Wyoming]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Sheridan County, Wyoming|Sheridan County]]\n| arrival_date    = March 11, 2020\n| origin          = [[California]], U.S.\n| confirmed_cases = 94<ref name=\"WDPHE-official\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) |url=https://www.arcgis.com/apps/MapSeries/index.html?appid=42fd398fa8f449fb930f2d3755c5a1bb |website=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| severe_cases    = \n| recovery_cases  = \n| deaths          = 0\n| territories     = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://covid19.wyo.gov/}}\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the U.S. state of [[Wyoming]] in March 2020. According to the [[Wyoming Department of Health]], there are 94 confirmed cases as of March 30, 2020. Responses in the state have included governmental action through the creation of task forces, industry actions, and the cancellation of sports seasons in the state.\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States/Wyoming medical cases chart}}\n* March 11, 2020: First reported case of [[COVID-19]] is a woman in [[Sheridan County]] who recently travelled domestically.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/first-coronavirus-case-reported-in-wyoming/article_0b075aea-a3ab-58d8-b5bd-a5b03b764075.html|title=First coronavirus case reported in Wyoming|date=11 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-date=18 March 2020|work=[[Casper Star-Tribune]]|archive-url=https://archive.is/gvGMO\n}}</ref><ref name=\"LA Times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-03-19/coronavirus-wyoming-covid-19-casper-idaho|title=Think the most isolated corners of the U.S. are safe from coronavirus? Think again|first=Maria L.|last=La Ganga|newspaper=[[LA Times]]|date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* March 13, 2020: Second reported case is a man in Fremont County.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/second-wyoming-case-of-coronavirus-identified/article_1945cbeb-a94d-542d-b08c-26c3fa58dc2f.html|title=Second Wyoming case of coronavirus identified|date=13 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|archive-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://archive.is/fLKQt|work=Casper Star-Tribune}}</ref>\n* March 15, 2020: Governor Gordon recommends closing all public schools.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oilcity.news/community/health/covid-19/2020/03/15/natrona-county-school-district-closing-schools-starting-monday-amid-covid-19-pandemic/|title=Natrona County School District Closind Schools Starting Monday Amid COVID-19 Pandemic|date=15 March 2020|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=http://archive.is/iGLID|work=Oil City News}}</ref>\n* March 18, 2020: Third positive case in [[Cheyenne, Wyoming]], brings the state count up to 16 confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://trib.com/news/local/casper/third-person-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-cheyenne-bringing-state/article_2b32b003-f677-512e-9286-e8c4de4988c3.html|date=18 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020|title=Third person tests positive for coronavirus in Cheyenne, bringing state total to 16|work=Casper Star-Tribune|archive-date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://archive.is/ncRIX}}</ref>\n\n==Responses==\nOn March 17, Wyoming Governor [[Mark Gordon (politician)|Mark Gordon]] \"announced the creation of five task forces designed to tackle the effects of the spreading coronavirus\", and condemned [[Hoarding (economics)|hoarding]] in the state.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trib.com/news/state-and-regional/health/wyoming-governor-announces-creation-of-five-task-forces-to-battle/article_428b9637-01b9-5533-ba53-af7a14542ce2.html|title=Wyoming governor announces creation of five task forces to battle effects of coronavirus|first1=Seth|last1=Klamann|first2=Morgan|last2=Hughes|publisher=[[Casper Star-Tribune]]|date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIndustries have had varying responses, with energy companies in the state trying to balance safety with continued productivity by imposing quarantine and travel restrictions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trib.com/business/energy/energy-companies-in-wyoming-intensify-response-to-coronavirus-outbreak/article_6fd14076-9f24-5655-8967-60ef7488b590.html|title=Energy companies in Wyoming intensify response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Camille|last=Erickson|publisher=Casper Star-Tribune|date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Impact on sports==\nIn college sports, the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] cancelled all winter and spring tournaments, most notably the [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|men]]'s and [[2020 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament|women]]'s basketball tournaments, affecting colleges and universities statewide.<ref name=\"ncaa\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ncaa.org/about/resources/media-center/news/ncaa-cancels-remaining-winter-and-spring-championships |title=NCAA cancels remaining winter and spring championships |last=Osburn |first=Stacey |date=March 12, 2020 |website=NCAA |access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref> On March 16, the [[National Junior College Athletic Association]] also canceled the remainder of the winter seasons as well as the spring seasons.<ref>{{Cite news |last=DeCamp |first=Scott |url=https://www.mlive.com/sports/2020/03/njcaa-cancels-spring-sports-basketball-nationals-amid-coronavirus-outbreak.html |title=NJCAA cancels spring sports, basketball nationals amid coronavirus outbreak |date=2020-03-16 |work=MLive.com |access-date=2020-03-25 |language=en}}</ref> High school sports were also cancelled.<ref name=\"LA Times\"/>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n! colspan=\"3\" |2019 Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) Cases in Wyoming\nUpdated March 30, 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livescience.com/wyoming-coronavirus.html|title=Wyoming: Latest updates on Coronavirus|last=March 2020|first=Kimberly Hickok-Reference Editor 18|website=livescience.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | County\n! scope=\"col\" | Confirmed Cases\n! scope=\"col\" | Deaths\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Albany County, Wyoming|Albany]]\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Big Horn County, Wyoming|Big Horn]]\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Campbell County, Wyoming|Campbell]]\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Carbon County, Wyoming|Carbon]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Converse County, Wyoming|Converse]]\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Crook County, Wyoming|Crook]]\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Fremont County, Wyoming|Fremont]]\n| 24\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Goshen County, Wyoming|Goshen]]\n| 1\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Hot Springs County, Wyoming|Hot Springs]]\n| 0\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Johnson County, Wyoming|Johnson]]\n| 5\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Laramie County, Wyoming|Laramie]]\n| 20\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lincoln County, Wyoming|Lincoln]]\n|0\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Natrona County, Wyoming|Natrona]]\n| 10\n| 0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Niobrara County, Wyoming|Niobrara]]\n| 0\